criteria.textblock:
        Inclusion Criteria:

          -  fluctuating muscle weakness and fatigability, along with one of the below:

          -  more than 10% amplitude decrement in low frequency repetitive nerve stimulation,less
             than 10% amplitude increment in high frequency repetitive nerve stimulation;

          -  anti-AChR or MuSK antibody positivity;

          -  positive to the neostigmine test;

          -  understanding and assigning the informed consent form, and having a good compliance
             with the follow up.

        Exclusion Criteria:

          -  excluding the possible diagnosis of Lambert-Eaton syndrome, congenital myasthenia
             syndrome,botulism injection, chronic progressive extraocular ophthalmoplegia, etc;

          -  participating other clinical trials;

          -  poor compliance to the follow up.
